iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories El -Arish - Egyptian security officials say that members of a prominent local tribe in northern Sinai have burned alive a suspected Islamic State militant.The officials say the man's charred body was found early on Wednesday south of the town of Rafah in the Sinai Peninsula. The officials spoke on condition of anonymity because they are not authorised to talk to reporters.They say the killing came just hours after an Islamic State suicide bomber attacked a tribal checkpoint in northern Sinai and killed four members of the Tarabeen tribe on Tuesday.The incident is the latest escalation in the conflict in the restive peninsula, where Egyptian forces have been battling a growing insurgency with local tribes mostly remaining on the sidelines.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.